      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FRENZY (8) hit the ground running from out wide and on speed early but faded and swamped late when 6th at this track in Grade 5 company. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Key runner on his best form. OUR REGARDS (6) was in the minor money with a respectable 25.29, finishing second in a Special conditions Veteran race at Shepparton last start. Harder here but expected to feature again. LADY RAPID (2) crossed over from out wide last start before finishing second (29.82) at Sandown in a Grade 5 over 515m. Yet to score from this box but has never missed the frame in two starts. Ready to find winning form. CHAMPLAIN (3) made it two minor placings on the trot when beaten third (34.50) in a Grade 4/5 at Sandown last time out.",
